{{Infobox book | image = Encyclopédie berbère.png | image_size = | alt = Official logo for the encyclopedia | caption = Official logo for the encyclopedia | author = {{flatlist| * 14 editors * 17 godfathers }} | audio_read_by = | title_orig = | orig_lang_code = | title_working = | translator = | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = [[France]] | language = [[French language|French]] | series = | release_number = | subject = | genre = [[Encyclopedia]] | set_in = | publisher = {{flatlist| * Édisud (1984–2010) * [[Peeters (publishing company)|Peeters]] (2010–)}} | publisher2 = | pub_date = 1984–present | english_pub_date = | published = | media_type = 37 fascicles, 3 in press<ref name="IREMAM" /> | pages = {{flatlist| * 100 p. (in average) * 124 cm}} | awards = | isbn = | isbn_note = | oclc = | dewey = | congress = | preceded_by = | followed_by = | native_wikisource = | wikisource = | notes = | exclude_cover = | website = ''{{URL|http://encyclopedieberbere.revues.org|Encyclopédie berbère}}'' at [[Centre pour l'Édition Électronique Ouverte|OpenEdition Journals]] }}
'''''Encyclopédie berbère''''' (English: ''Berber Encyclopaedia'') is a [[French language|French-language]] [[encyclopaedia]] dealing with subjects related to the [[Berbers]]. It was launched in 1984 under the aegis of [[UNESCO]] and is published by Editions Edisud. Its first editor-in-chief was [[Gabriel Camps]]. After his death in 2002, he was succeeded by [[Salem Chaker]], Professor of [[Berber languages]] at the [[Aix-Marseille University]] Volume 27 ("[[Kairouan]] - [[Kifan Bel-Ghomari]]") appeared in 2005.<ref name="IREMAM">{{Cite web|title=Iremam - 4. Etudes berbères|url=http://www.iremam.cnrs.fr/spip.php?article3017|language=fr|publisher=IREMAM|access-date=December 18, 2017}}</ref> ''Encyclopédie berbère'' joined from fascicle XXX (December 2010), the publishing house [[Peeters (publishing company)|Peeters Publishers]], already engaged in Berber studies field.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://iremam.cnrs.fr/spip.php?article104|title=L’Encyclopédie berbère|last=Sabine|first=Partouche|date=|website=Institut de recherches et d'études sur les mondes arabes et musulmans Iremam - UMR 7310|access-date=2018-02-25}}</ref>
