{{refimprove|date=December 2017}}
An '''''obambo''''' is a type of [[ghost]] among certain peoples of [[Central Africa]].<ref>{{cite book|last1=Spence|first1=Lewis|title=An Encyclopaedia of Occultism|date=1920|publisher=Courier Corporation|isbn=978-0486426136|page=299|url=https://books.google.com.au/books?id=nOcoAwAAQBAJ|accessdate=18 December 2017}}</ref>
Obambo
An ''obambo'' initially resides in the [[The Bush|bush]], but eventually gets tired of this and appears to a close relative, requesting that he build a house for him near his own. That night the village women are gathered to dance and sing, and next day the people visit the grave of the deceased and make a rough idol. They then erect a little hut near the house of the person the ''obambo'' visited; then place the [[bier]] on which the deceased was carried to his grave inside the hut, as well as some of the dust from the grave. A white cloth is then draped over the door.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Bane|first1=Theresa|title=Encyclopedia of Spirits and Ghosts in World Mythology|date=March 10, 2016|publisher=McFarland|isbn=978-1476663555|page=97|url=https://books.google.com.au/books?id=VSu6CwAAQBAJ|accessdate=18 December 2017}}</ref>
An alternative meaning is the ghost of somebody who died in the bush and has no grave.
